            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Sirōmos",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Herod. vii. 98) is another form of Hiram, as Bertheau supposes, is more than doubtful. It is interesting to find that the king of Tyre bore this name in the time of Tiglath-pileser II., to whom he paid tribute (B.C. 738), along with Menahem of Samaria. (Assyr. ",
            "children": []
